<% content_for :title, "Lewsnetter — AI-native email marketing" %>
<% content_for :description, "Open-source email marketing built for agents. Visual segments, MCP-native, ships through your own SES." %>

<div class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50">

  <%# ============================================================
      Top bar — minimal. Logo on the left, sign-in on the right.
      ============================================================ %>
  <header class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 font-semibold tracking-tight">
        <span class="font-mono text-[15px]">Lewsnetter</span>
        <span class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-orange-50 text-orange-700 dark:bg-orange-950 dark:text-orange-300">Beta</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-5 text-sm">
        <a href="https://github.com/bborn/lewsnetter" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-zinc-600 hover:text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-300 dark:hover:text-zinc-50">GitHub</a>
        <%= link_to "Sign in", app_sign_in_url, class: "text-zinc-600 hover:text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-300 dark:hover:text-zinc-50" %>
        <%= link_to "Start free", app_sign_up_url, class: "button" %>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <%# ============================================================
      Hero — one-liner, sub, CTAs. Anti-bubble: no gradients, no
      stock illustrations. Geist + zinc + a single orange accent.
      ============================================================ %>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-400 mb-6">
        Open source · Self-host or use ours
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.05] text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-6">
        Email marketing<br>built for agents.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-2xl">
        Lewsnetter is a newsletter platform where every action a human can take, an AI agent can take too. Visual segment builder, MCP-native, ships through your own Amazon SES.
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
        <%= link_to "Start free — no card", app_sign_up_url, class: "button text-base px-6 py-3" %>
        <a href="#how" class="button-secondary text-base px-6 py-3">How it works</a>
        <span class="text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 ml-2">Free during beta · Open source</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%# ============================================================
      Differentiator row — three things, ordered by uniqueness.
      Each is a card-less stack: mono eyebrow + title + body.
      ============================================================ %>
  <section class="border-t border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">

      <div>
        <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">01 · Agent-native</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">MCP server out of the box</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          43 tools across campaigns, subscribers, segments, sending. Connect Claude or any MCP-compatible client and your agent can draft, segment, schedule, and send — using the same APIs the UI does. No second integration to build.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">02 · Bring your own SES</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Your AWS, your reputation</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          Plug your Amazon SES credentials in once via the guided setup wizard. Every campaign ships from your account, your sending reputation, your bill. We never see the outbound mail.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">03 · Real segmentation</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Visual builder, Intercom-style</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          Nested AND/OR groups, type-aware operators, live match count + sample rows as you build. Sync subscribers from your Rails app with the
          <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[13px] font-mono">lewsnetter-rails</code>
          gem and segment on anything you push.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <%# ============================================================
      How it works — three steps, numbered. No screenshots yet (we'll
      add them as we capture good ones). For now: descriptive copy
      that orients the reader.
      ============================================================ %>
  <section id="how" class="border-t border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-50 dark:bg-zinc-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
        <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">How it works</div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-3">From zero to first send in 5 minutes.</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          The guided setup wizard walks you through AWS SES credentials, sender verification, and a test send — so you know everything works before you ever queue a campaign.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <li class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-600 text-white font-mono text-sm mb-4">1</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-2">Sign up + connect SES</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
            Paste your AWS access keys. We verify them with SES, list your verified identities, and you import one as a sender — one click.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-600 text-white font-mono text-sm mb-4">2</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-2">Sync your audience</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
            CSV upload, JSON API, or the
            <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-[12px] font-mono">lewsnetter-rails</code>
            gem for live sync from your app. Subscribers come in with whatever attributes you want to segment on.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-600 text-white font-mono text-sm mb-4">3</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-2">Compose + ship</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
            MJML templates, Markdown body, Liquid for personalization. Or hand the whole thing to an agent over MCP. Bounce + complaint tracking works automatically.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%# ============================================================
      Tech + transparency strip — for the developers + privacy-aware
      audience this product attracts. Honest about what's there.
      ============================================================ %>
  <section class="border-t border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <div>
        <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">For developers</div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-4">
          Open source.<br>Self-host if you want.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          MIT-licensed. Rails 8 + SQLite + Litestream + Kamal. One-box deploy. Use the hosted version if you don't want to operate it; clone the repo if you do.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <a href="https://github.com/bborn/lewsnetter" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button-secondary">View on GitHub →</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/bborn/lewsnetter/tree/master/gems/lewsnetter-rails" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button-secondary">Rails gem</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest font-mono text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">What's actually under the hood</div>
        <dl class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 pb-2">
            <dt class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Framework</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 font-mono text-xs">Rails 8 + Bullet Train</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 pb-2">
            <dt class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Database</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 font-mono text-xs">SQLite + Litestream → R2</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 pb-2">
            <dt class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Sending</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 font-mono text-xs">Your Amazon SES</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 pb-2">
            <dt class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Agent layer</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 font-mono text-xs">MCP + ruby_llm</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 pb-2">
            <dt class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">PII at rest</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 font-mono text-xs">AES-GCM encrypted</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between pb-2">
            <dt class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Pricing</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 font-mono text-xs">Free during beta</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%# ============================================================
      Closing CTA — keep simple. One ask.
      ============================================================ %>
  <section class="border-t border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-50 dark:bg-zinc-900">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-4">
        Ship your first campaign tonight.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Sign up, connect SES, send yourself a test — about 5 minutes. Then queue something real.
      </p>
      <%= link_to "Start free", app_sign_up_url, class: "button text-base px-6 py-3" %>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
